data.title: Midweek Music & Market: BOB, The Music of Dylan
data.meta_description: Music, games, food trucks, a farmers market and more await at Bloomington Civic Plaza, Wednesdays in July and August.
data.text:
Featuring award winning musicians from the Twin Cities, BOB! The Music of Dylan artfully covers many old and new Bob Dylan songs.

Food vendors: Brick Oven Bus, Coastal Coolers, Eggroll Queen, Heavy Metal Grill, Pharaohâ€™s Gyros, Sambusa Samosa

Beer vendor: Northstar Tavern

Midweek Music & Market offers a great mix of food, beer, music, games, and fun on Wednesdays in July and August in the east lot at Bloomington Civic Plaza.

Market, food and beverage sales open 5 - 8 p.m.

Music performances begin at 5:30 p.m.

The area where music is performed on the Civic Plaza East Lawn is a grass hill with no permanent seating. Please consider bringing a blanket or lawn chair for your comfort and convenience while enjoying the music.
